<Layout title="About — Nellie Borrero" description="Former Global Inclusion & Diversity Senior Strategic Advisor at Accenture, global speaker, author, and media commentator." path="/about">
	<section class="container py-12 grid gap-8 md:grid-cols-3 items-start">
		<div class="md:col-span-2 prose">
			<h1 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-plum">Today's Voice for Inclusion</h1>
			<div class="space-y-4 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
				<p><strong>Former Global Inclusion & Diversity Senior Strategic Advisor, Accenture</strong><br>
				Global speaker • Author, Media Commentator</p>
				
				<p><strong>Recognitions:</strong> Hispanic IT Executive Council's prestigious Estrella Award 2023, Hall of Fame 2022, LatinaStyle Highest Ranking Latina 2021; Top 30 Diversity & Inclusion Leaders 2022 LeadersHum</p>

				<p>Under Nellie's pioneering leadership—a first-generation Latina—Accenture underwent a profound transformation in its approach to Inclusion and Diversity (I&D). She steered the company away from deep-rooted biases, leading Accenture to become the #1 ranked employer for inclusion, diversity, and equity in the United States.</p>

				<p>She created a global career development program for women, led the strategic positioning of the company's LGBTQI+ and Persons with Disability agendas and the design of multiple ethnic diversity-focused programs.</p>

				<p>Nellie is a highly respected global speaker and media commentator called on to address bold leadership and the business—and personal—value of committing to build and foster inclusive workplaces.</p>

				<p>Nellie serves on the HITEC board, as a member of the Women's Forum of New York, and as Latino Corporate Directors Association and Chief.</p>
			</div>

